        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 2:31PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 231 PM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm near Lake Tobesofkee, or 12 miles northeast of
Roberta, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, frequent cloud to ground
lightning and increased chance of a brief tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...While winds should result in minor damage to tree limbs and
blowing around of light, unsecured objects, this storm has
also exhibited localized rotation. A brief tornado could
quickly form.

Locations impacted include...
Macon, Payne, Payne City, Cross Keys, Wesleyan, Dry Branch, Lizella,
Lake Tobesofkee, Skipperton, Rutland, and Franklinton.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central Georgia.</instruction>
